        "\n",
        "Scope of the document\n",
        "\n",
        "This Algorithm Theoretical Basis Document (ATBD) describes the atmospheric correction (AC) processing chain for deriving Top-of-Canopy (TOC) directional reflectances from Top-of-Atmosphere (TOA) reflectances measured by the Proba-V/VGT sensors. The processing implements rigorous uncertainty propagation following the FIDUCEO (Fidelity and Uncertainty in Climate Data Records from Earth Observations) methodology.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "The processing follows a hierarchical structure:\n",
        "\n",
        "**Level 1C** → **Level 2A** (atmospherically corrected pixels)\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│                    INPUT DATA                           │\n",
        "├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n",
        "│  • TOA reflectances (B1, B2, B3, B4) + uncertainties    │\n",
        "│  • Geometry (SZA, VZA, SAA, VAA)                        │\n",
        "│  • Geolocation (lat, lon)                               │\n",
        "│  • Status map (cloud mask)                              │\n",
        "└────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                 │\n",
        "                 ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│              AUXILIARY DATA RETRIEVAL                   │\n",
        "├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n",
        "│  • DEM → altitude z, uncertainty Δz                     │\n",
        "│  • MERRA-2 → P₀, T, UO₃, UH₂O, τa⁵⁵⁰, aerosol species   │\n",
        "│  • AMIP ensemble → aerosol model uncertainty            │\n",
        "└────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                 │\n",
        "                 ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│         ATMOSPHERIC CORRECTION (SMAC-CL)                │\n",
        "├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n",
        "│  Process 1: Direct atmospheric correction               │\n",
        "│  Process 2: Uncertainty propagation                     │\n",
        "│    - Analytical Jacobians (Rtoa, UO₃, UH₂O)             │\n",
        "│    - Finite difference Jacobians (Ps, τa⁵⁵⁰)            │\n",
        "│    - Ensemble uncertainty (aerosol model)               │\n",
        "│  Process 3: Radiative transfer approximation errors     │\n",
        "└────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                 │\n",
        "                 ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│                    OUTPUT DATA                          │\n",
        "├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n",
        "│  • TOC reflectances (B1, B2, B3, B4)                    │\n",
        "│  • Total uncertainty ΔRtoc                              │\n",
        "│  • Optionally, Uncertainty components by source         │\n",
        "│  • Quality flags                                        │\n",
        "└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "## What's New in v1.1\n",
        "\n",
        "This v1.1 revision keeps the full v1.0 content below **unchanged** and adds the following new material:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Appendix D: Implementation Notes** — performance optimizations (ancillary Zarr cache, tile-based processing, local output file, single NetCDF handle, DEM cropping, copy-on-write shared state), the float32 overflow fix for `SLP`/`T10M`, and known limitations (adjacency effects, Köppen-Geiger regionalization).\n",
        "- **Appendix E: SMACCL OpenCL Kernel API** — the Python host wrapper API (`Smaccl.run`), the OpenCL kernel signature (`devicecl.cl`), the output variable mapping, and the `ISmaccl` product-level wrapper API, as implemented in the HYGEOS `smaccl` repository.\n",
        "- A **critical bug-fix note** on surface pressure computation: `SLP` and `T10M` must be stored as float32 (not float16) in the ancillary cache to avoid overflow in `log(R·T)` (see Appendix D.2 and the note under Effect 4: Surface Pressure Uncertainty).\n",
        "- Confirmation that **DEM interpolation** uses linear interpolation (an improvement over the nearest-neighbor method originally specified), and that **adjacency effects** and **Köppen-Geiger regionalization** are, respectively, a known limitation and a planned feature.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Input and Auxiliary Data\n",
        "\n",
        "## Level 1C Input Data\n",
        "\n",
        "The data used as inputs are Proba-V-VGT1-VGT2 Top-Of-Atmosphere reflectances in 4 spectral bands (Table 5) and associated geometrical information and basic classification flags. Let us note that the viewing geometry could be different between VIS-NIR and SWIR bands. The RSRF's of each band is slightly different between the 3 cameras labelled LEFT, CENTER and RIGHT that cover Proba-V field of view but one RSRF's for VGTs. The philosophy of the AC algorithm is to process the data band per band without the use of any spectral, spatial or temporal features. Therefore, the format of the input data is not important and the processing of individual pixels for selected bands or an entire Level 1 tile is similar.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Spectral Bands** (Proba-V example):\n",
        "\n",
        "+----------+-------------------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Band     | Central wavelength (nm) | FWHM (nm) | Corrected | Absorbing gas/ transmission\\*               |\n",
        "+:=========+:========================+:==========+:==========+:============================================+\n",
        "| B1       | 463.5                   | 47.0      | yes       | O~3~ (0.994)                                |\n",
        "+----------+-------------------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| B2       | 655.0                   | 80.0      | yes       | O~3~ (0.976); H~2~O (0.989); O~2~ (0.981)   |\n",
        "+----------+-------------------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| B3       | 839.0                   | 130.0     | yes       | O~3~ (0.999); H~2~O (0.893); O~2~ (0.999)   |\n",
        "+----------+-------------------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| B4       | 1602.5                  | 65.0      | yes       | CO~2~ (0.969); H~2~O (0.995); CH~4~ (0.998) |\n",
        "+----------+-------------------------+-----------+-----------+---------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "Table 1: VGT's spectral bands and potential atmospheric gaseous absorbers\n",
        "\n",
        "**Required Variables per Pixel:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- TOA-r(λ): Top-of-atmosphere reflectance for each band\n",
        "- DTOA-r(λ): TOA reflectance uncertainty\n",
        "- Viewing and solar azimuth angles (VAA, VAA_SWIR and SAA) \\[0, 360°\\]\n",
        "- Viewing and solar zenith angles (VZA, VZA_SWIR and SZA) \\[0, 90°\\].\n",
        "- Geolocation: latitude, longitude\n",
        "- Status Map: Cloud mask flags\n",
        "\n",
        "## Digital Elevation Model (DEM)\n",
        "\n",
        "The GTOPO30 (Global 30 Arc-Second Elevation) dataset is used for assigning a surface elevation to each pixel. It is downloaded as a set of binary files (<https://lta.cr.usgs.gov/GTOPO30>) and then re-assembled as a unique [NetCDF]{.underline} file.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Frequency: Static\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial Grid: 2D, full extent of latitude from 90 degrees south to 90 degrees north, and the full extent of longitude from 180 degrees west to 180 degrees east. The horizontal grid spacing is 30-arc seconds.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Dimensions of 21,600 rows and 43,200 columns. The horizontal coordinate system is decimal degrees of latitude and longitude referenced to WGS84.\n",
        "\n",
        "- The vertical units represent elevation above mean sea level (elev) and are expressed in meters. The values range from -407 to 8,752. It is complemented by the spatial standard deviation of the altitude (Delev in meters) computed in 3x3 pixel boxes.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Specifications:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial resolution: 30 arc-seconds (\\~1 km)\n",
        "- Coverage: Global (-90° to +90° lat, -180° to +180° lon)\n",
        "- Dimensions: 21,600 rows × 43,200 columns\n",
        "- Vertical range: -407 to +8,752 m above mean sea level\n",
        "- Additional field: **Delev** - standard deviation of altitude computed in 3×3 pixel boxes (proxy for geolocation uncertainty impact)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Usage:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "z = elev(lat, lon)           # Surface elevation\n",
        "Δz = Delev(lat, lon)         # Elevation uncertainty\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "> **Implementation Note (v1.1):** the implementation uses **linear interpolation** (via `scipy.interpolate.RegularGridInterpolator`) to sample `elev`/`Delev` at the satellite grid, rather than nearest-neighbor. This is a reasonable improvement, giving smoother elevation transitions at tile boundaries; the impact is negligible given the 90 m GTOPO30 resolution versus \\~1 km VGT pixels. The global DEM is also cropped to the product's lat/lon extent before loading (\\~1.9 GB → \\~0.2 GB), see Appendix D.1.\n",
        "\n",
        "## MERRA-2 Reanalysis Products\n",
        "\n",
        "The Modern-Era Retrospective analysis for Research and Applications version 2 (MERRA-2) is a NASA atmospheric reanalysis for the satellite era using the Goddard Earth Observing System Model, Version 5 (GEOS-5) with its Atmospheric Data Assimilation System (ADAS), version 5.12.4. It is the data source for all atmospheric parameters (<https://gmao.gsfc.nasa.gov/reanalysis/MERRA-2/>). The README file for the [NetCDF]{.underline} MERRA-2 products is available here:\n",
        "\n",
        "(<https://goldsmr4.gesdisc.eosdis.nasa.gov/data/MERRA2/M2I1NXINT.5.12.4/doc/MERRA2.README.pdf>), while the full product specification is available here:\n",
        "\n",
        "(<https://gmao.gsfc.nasa.gov/pubs/docs/Bosilovich785.pdf>).\n",
        "\n",
        "The datasets are available from 1^st^ January 1980 until present. They can be downloaded from several sites, for example ([https://disc.sci.gsfc.nasa.gov/daac-bin/FTPSubset2.pl](https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fdisc.sci.gsfc.nasa.gov%2Fdaac-bin%2FFTPSubset2.pl&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNHxhCMbiw1OeM3uf72kiq0W9oLYrg)).\n",
        "\n",
        "Two products are currently used for all atmospheric parameters:\n",
        "\n",
        "- tavg1_2d_slv_Nx: 2-dimensional, 1-Hourly, Time-Averaged for physical parameters, ozone and water vapour.\n",
        "\n",
        "- tavg1_2d_aer_Nx: 2-dimensional, 1-Hourly, Time-Averaged for aerosol diagnostics.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Overview:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Temporal coverage: 1980-present\n",
        "- Temporal resolution: 1-hourly, from 00:30 UTC (time average)\n",
        "- Spatial grid: 0.5° × 0.625°\n",
        "  - 361 lat (from -90 to 90)\n",
        "  - 576 lon (from -180 to 179.375)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Retrieved Parameters:**\n",
        "\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| Variable     | MERRA-2 ID | Description                         | Units         |\n",
        "+:=============+:===========+:====================================+:==============+\n",
        "| UO₃          | TO3        | Total column ozone                  | Dobson units  |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| UH₂O         | TQV        | Total precipitable water vapor      | kg·m⁻²        |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| P₀           | SLP        | Sea-level pressure                  | Pa            |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| T            | T10M       | Temperature at 10m                  | K             |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(total) | TOTEXTTAU  | Total aerosol extinction AOD\\@550nm | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(BC)    | BCEXTTAU   | Black carbon AOD\\@550nm             | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(OC)    | OCEXTTAU   | Organic carbon AOD\\@550nm           | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(DU)    | DUEXTTAU   | Dust AOD\\@550nm                     | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(SU)    | SUEXTTAU   | Sulfate AOD\\@550nm                  | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "| τa⁵⁵⁰(SS)    | SSEXTTAU   | Sea salt AOD\\@550nm                 | dimensionless |\n",
        "+--------------+------------+-------------------------------------+---------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "**Interpolation Method:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial: Bilinear interpolation to pixel location\n",
        "- Temporal: Linear interpolation between hourly time steps\n",
        "\n",
        "## MERRA-2 AMIP Ensemble for Aerosol Uncertainty\n",
        "\n",
        "The purpose of this dataset is to estimate aerosol model uncertainty through ensemble spread\n",
        "\n",
        "The MERRA-2 AMIP (Atmospheric Model Intercomparison Project) dataset consists of a 10-member ensemble of free-running simulations with the GEOS atmospheric model (<https://gmao.gsfc.nasa.gov/gmao-products/merra-2/merra-2-amip_merra-2/>) . The model version, along with imposed boundary conditions, is configured identically to the GEOS model used in the MERRA-2 reanalysis dataset. It covers the years from 1980 to 2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset can be accessed here (<https://portal.nccs.nasa.gov/datashare/gmao_m2amip/>). It is organized in 10 directories, one for each run of the ensemble (example m2amip01), then one directory for each year and then one directory per month. This monthly average dataset is used for estimating the spread of the aerosol optical thickness between models and is supposed to be a proxy for the uncertainty on the MERRA-2 AOT's. The spatial grid is the same as MERRA2 daily data described in section 2.3.\n",
        "\n",
        "The file we are using is tavgM_2d_aer_Nx.YYYYMM.nc4 with the same parameters as in section 2.3\n",
        "\n",
        "[Note]{.underline} : For Proba-V data in 2018 to 2020, it is expected to use AMIP data of 2017 for the corresponding month.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Description:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- 10-member ensemble of GEOS atmospheric model free-running simulations\n",
        "- Same model version and boundary conditions as MERRA-2 reanalysis\n",
        "- Period: 1980-2017 (for 2018-2020 data, use 2017 corresponding month)\n",
        "- Product: `tavgM_2d_aer_Nx` (monthly averages)\n",
        "- Variables: Same aerosol species as MERRA-2 (TOTEXTTAU, DUEXTTAU, etc.)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implementation:**\n",
        "\n",
        "``` For each ensemble member j (j=``1..``10): ```\\\n",
        "``` ``τa,AMIPj``⁵⁵⁰(species) = spatially interpolate monthly mean ```\n",
        "\n",
        "## SMAC Coefficients Database\n",
        "\n",
        "**Description**: Pre-computed coefficients for 148 aerosol models covering realistic atmospheric mixtures (see Section 8)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Coverage:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Sensors: VGT1, VGT2, Proba-V (LEFT, CENTER, RIGHT cameras)\n",
        "- Aerosol models: 148 mixtures of 5 basic components (DU, SU, OC, BC, SS)\n",
        "- Relative humidity: Fixed at 80%\n",
        "\n",
        "**Content per aerosol model:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Gaseous absorption coefficients (O₃, H₂O, CO₂, CH₄)\n",
        "- Aerosol scattering coefficients\n",
        "- Look-up tables for atmospheric functions\n",
        "\n",
        "## C3S Surface Albedo product (experimental)\n",
        "\n",
        "This product gives a background BRDF shape to estimate the surface BRDF effects on atmospheric correction. The dataset is available on VITO infrastructure and is described here (<https://dast.copernicus-climate.eu/documents/satellite-albedo/D1.3.4-v2.0_ATBD_CDR_SA_MULTI_SENSOR_v2.0_PRODUCTS_v1.1.pdf>).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Description**:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Ten days Surface BRDF kernel model parameters (k~0~,k~1~,k~2~) from C3S Surface Albedo project (see section 8.5 for a mathematical description).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Overview :**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Temporal coverage: VGT 1998-2014\n",
        "\n",
        "- Temporal resolution: 10 days\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial resolution: 1km\n",
        "\n",
        "- Spatial grid: 10°x10° tiles\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implementation** :\n",
        "\n",
        "Computing and spatially interpolate from them two normalized parameters $k_{1}^{p}\\ and\\ k_{2}^{p}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "$$k_{1}^{p} = \\ \\frac{k_{1}}{k_{0}}\\ ;\\ k_{2}^{p} = \\ \\frac{k_{2}}{k_{0}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "# Atmospheric corrections algorithm\n",
        "\n",
        "## SMAC Algorithm Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "Pixels are considered for atmospheric correction if they are not marked as \"cloud-covered\" or \"contaminated\" in the cloud mask of input data. TOC directional reflectance estimates are obtained by applying SMAC (Rahman and Dedieu, 1994), a Simplified Method for the Atmospheric Correction of satellite measurements in the solar spectrum to the TOA reflectances.\n",
        "\n",
        "The choice of the SMAC algorithm is supported by the following arguments:\n",
        "\n",
        "- It is **operational** and largely used in the land community and already implemented in the Copernicus Global Land Service and Proba-V processing lines.\n",
        "\n",
        "- It is a **robust and generic** algorithm; thus, it minimizes the dependence on the sensor which is a good thing when one wants to build a multi sensor long time series with limited biases.\n",
        "\n",
        "- The correction algorithm is based on the 6S radiative transfer formulation of the satellite signal (Vermote et al., 1997) and is **analytical** It is thus adapted to an error propagation analysis.\n",
        "\n",
        "**In our implementation, all the pertinent radiative quantities are parameterized as a function of auxiliary gridded data** as described in the section 2:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Gas content (mainly ozone and water vapor for the spectral channels considered in this project)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Aerosol content and aerosol type\n",
        "\n",
        "- Molecular scattering mainly driven by the sea-level surface pressure and the surface elevation.\n",
        "\n",
        "This approach is justified by increasing **accuracy** of the Reanalysis datasets like MERRA-2 or CAMS, which are **not sensors biased, without spatial, temporal or spectral gaps**. It is particularly well adapted to the reprocessing of Fundamental Climate Data Records.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Equations\n",
        "\n",
        "All the parametrization is contained in the SMAC coefficients.\n",
        "\n",
        "+-------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------+\n",
        "|       | $$T = T_{g}\\left( \\theta_{s},\\theta_{v} \\right)T_{sca}\\left( \\theta_{s} \\right)T_{sca}\\left( \\theta_{v} \\right)$$ | \\(1\\) |\n",
        "+=======+:==================================================================================================================+:======+\n",
        "|       | $$R = R_{toa} - R_{atm}\\left( \\theta_{s},\\theta_{v},\\Delta\\Phi \\right)T_{g}\\left( \\theta_{s},\\theta_{v} \\right)$$ | \\(2\\) |\n",
        "+-------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------+\n",
        "|       | $$R_{toc}\\left( \\theta_{s},\\theta_{v},\\Delta\\Phi \\right) = \\frac{R}{T + s_{atm}R}$$                               | \\(3\\) |\n",
        "+-------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------+\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **T**: Total atmospheric transmission\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **T~g~**: Gaseous transmission (O₃, H₂O, CO₂, CH₄)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **T~sca~**: Scattering transmission (Rayleigh + aerosol)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **R**: Intermediate corrected reflectance\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **R~atm~**: Atmospheric path radiance\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **s~atm~**: Atmospheric spherical albedo\n",
        "\n",
        "## Sensitivities\n",
        "\n",
        "It is possible to derive the atmospherically corrected TOC directional reflectance uncertainty $\\Delta R_{toc}$ from the **uncertainties on the TOA reflectance**, on the **atmospheric reflectances and transmittances**, which are themselves derived from the **uncertainties** **on the** **gaseous content**, **surface pressure** **aerosol load and model**. The sensitivities (Jacobians) to the inputs are obtained in the following manner\n",
        "\n",
        "### Sensitivity to TOA reflectance\n",
        "\n",
        "The radiometric uncertainty of the TOA reflectance is$\\ \\mathrm{\\Delta}R_{toa}$. The resulting uncertainty about the TOC directional reflectance$\\ \\mathrm{\\Delta}_{R_{toc}}^{R_{toa}}$, is obtained:\n",
        "\n",
        "+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                                               |\n",
        "+:=============================================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$\\mathrm{\\Delta}_{R_{toc}}^{R_{toa}} = \\left| \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}}{\\partial R_{toa}}.\\mathrm{\\Delta}R_{toa} \\right|$$ (4) |\n",
        "+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\frac{\\partial R_{toc}}{\\partial R_{toa}}$ is the sensitivity of TOC directional reflectance to any change in TOA reflectance. It is the Jacobian$\\ J_{R_{toc}}^{R_{toa}}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Within SMAC, it can be derived analytically:\n",
        "\n",
        "+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                          |\n",
        "+:========================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$J_{R_{toc}}^{R_{toa}} = \\ \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}}{\\partial R}\\frac{\\partial R}{\\partial R_{toa}}$$ (5) |\n",
        "+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "after remarking that$\\ \\frac{\\partial R}{\\partial R_{toa}} = 1,$ and using Eqs. 2 and 3\n",
        "\n",
        "+----------+------------------------------------------+----------+\n",
        "|          | $$\\eta = \\frac{1}{({T + s}_{atm}\\ R)}$$  | \\(6\\)    |\n",
        "+==========+:=========================================+:=========+\n",
        "|          | $$J_{R_{toc}}^{R_{toa}} = \\eta^{2}\\ T$$  | \\(7\\)    |\n",
        "+----------+------------------------------------------+----------+\n",
        "\n",
        "### Sensitivity to Ozone and Water Vapor\n",
        "\n",
        "The sensitivity of TOC directional reflectance to the uncertainty in the total column of either ozone or water vapor is also treated analytically within SMAC. In the following, we applied the equation for gas X, with X being O~3~ or H~2~O.\n",
        "\n",
        "The uncertainty in the total column $U_{X}$ is propagated through the Jacobian$\\ J_{R_{toc}}^{U_{X}}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                     |\n",
        "+:===================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$\\mathrm{\\Delta}_{R_{toc}}^{U_{X}} = \\left| J_{R_{toc}}^{U_{X}}.\\mathrm{\\Delta}U_{X} \\right|$$ (8) |\n",
        "+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "Within SMAC, it can also be derived analytically.\n",
        "\n",
        "Let us recall the formulation of the transmission of the gas $T_{X}$:\n",
        "\n",
        "|                                                   |\n",
        "|:-------------------------------------------------:|\n",
        "| $${T_{X} = e}^{{{\\ a_{X}(U}_{X}m)}^{n_{X}}}$$ (9) |\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "where $a_{X}$ and $n_{X}$ are SMAC coefficients and m is the air mass:\n",
        "\n",
        "|                                                                  |\n",
        "|:----------------------------------------------------------------:|\n",
        "| $$m = \\frac{1}{\\cos\\theta_{s}} + \\frac{1}{\\cos\\theta_{v}}$$ (10) |\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "We decompose Jacobian into two parts:\n",
        "\n",
        "+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                              |\n",
        "+:============================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$J_{R_{toc}}^{U_{X}} = \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}}{\\partial T_{X}}.\\frac{\\partial T_{X}}{\\partial U_{X}}$$ (11) |\n",
        "+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "The sensitivity of $T_{X}$ to $U_{X}$ is:\n",
        "\n",
        "+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                                        |\n",
        "+:======================================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$\\frac{\\partial T_{X}}{\\partial U_{X}} = {\\left( \\frac{a_{X}.n_{X}}{U_{X}} \\right).{\\ (U}_{X}m)}^{n_{X}}.T_{X}$$ (12) |\n",
        "+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "The sensitivity of TOC directional reflectance to $T_{X}$ is obtained through Eqs. and using the decomposition${\\ T}_{g} = T_{X}{\\ .T}_{noX}$:\n",
        "\n",
        "+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                       |\n",
        "+:=====================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$\\frac{\\partial R_{toc}}{\\partial T_{X}} = {- \\eta}^{2}\\frac{TR_{toa}}{T_{X}}$$ (13) |\n",
        "+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "### Surface Pressure and AOT at 550 nm\n",
        "\n",
        "For the surface pressure ${\\ P}_{s}$ and the AOT at 550 nm${\\ \\tau}_{a}^{550}$, we process the pixel two times more with small perturbations $\\delta P_{s}$ and$\\ \\delta\\tau_{a}^{550}$, and then derive the Jacobians using the finite differences:\n",
        "\n",
        "+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                                                      |\n",
        "+:====================================================================================================================================:+\n",
        "| $$J_{R_{toc}}^{P_{s}} = \\frac{{R_{toc}\\left( P_{s} \\right) - \\rho}_{toc}\\left( P_{s} - \\delta P_{s} \\right)}{\\delta P_{s}}\\ ,$$ (14) |\n",
        "+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "+-------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------+\n",
        "|       | $\\mathrm{\\Delta}_{R_{toc}}^{P_{s}} = \\left| J_{R_{toc}}^{P_{s}}.\\mathrm{\\Delta}P_{s} \\right|$,                                                                         | \\(15\\) |\n",
        "+=======+:=======================================================================================================================================================================+:=======+\n",
        "|       | $$J_{R_{toc}}^{\\tau_{a}^{550}} = \\frac{{R_{toc}\\left( \\tau_{a}^{550} \\right) - R}_{toc}\\left( \\tau_{a}^{550} - \\delta\\tau_{a}^{550} \\right)}{\\delta\\tau_{a}^{550}}\\ $$ | \\(16\\) |\n",
        "+-------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------+\n",
        "|       | $$\\mathrm{\\Delta}_{R_{toc}}^{\\tau_{a}^{550}} = \\left| J_{R_{toc}}^{\\tau_{a}^{550}}.\\mathrm{\\Delta}\\tau_{a}^{550} \\right|$$                                             | \\(17\\) |\n",
        "+-------+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------+\n",
        "\n",
        "We use$\\ \\delta P_{s} = 10\\ hPa,\\ \\delta\\tau_{a}^{550} = 0.1\\ \\tau_{a}^{550}$. These values are chosen to provoke a sufficient response in the AC scheme and still stay in the linear regime\n",
        "\n",
        "# Validation Strategy\n",
        "\n",
        "TOC-r's obtained with several aerosol ancillary data are validated with in-situ reference product obtained from AERONET data (version 3 of inverted AOD, spectral index of refraction and volume particle size distribution) and the 6S accurate atmospheric correction method. The comparison is made for N=48 AERONET sites (see Table 1) that cover different biomes, locations and meteorological conditions. Extraction of Proba-V data TOA-r and TOC-r' are done for 300 m products and TOA-r are processed with the 6S atmospheric correction software with AERONET data as inputs as it is done in the ACIX project (see Figure 1). TOC-r are evaluated using the same metrics as in ACIX\n",
        "\n",
        "$A = \\frac{1}{N}\\left( \\sum_{i = 1}^{N}{\\Delta{toc\\_ r}_{i}^{}} \\right)$, Accuracy\n",
        "\n",
        "$P = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{N - 1}\\left( \\sum_{i = 1}^{N}\\left( \\Delta{toc\\_ r}_{i}^{} - A \\right)^{2} \\right)}$, Precision\n",
        "\n",
        "$U = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{N_{}}\\sum_{i = 1}^{N_{}}\\left( \\Delta{toc\\_ r}_{i}^{} \\right)^{2}}$, Uncertainty\n",
        "\n",
        "with$\\ \\Delta{toc\\_ r}_{i}^{} = \\left( {toc\\_ r}_{i}^{processor} - \\ {toc\\_ r}_{i}^{Aeronet} \\right)$,\n",
        "\n",
        "![](./media/media/image1.png){width=\"5.409448818897638in\" height=\"2.952755905511811in\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "Figure : Validation methodology logic\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.content-visible when-format=\"docx\"}\n",
        "![](./media/media/image2.emf){width=\"5.8125in\" height=\"3.1775317147856517in\"}\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.content-visible when-format=\"pdf\"}\n",
        "*(Figure omitted in PDF export: original diagram is a Windows EMF vector graphic not convertible in this environment; see the DOCX version of this ATBD for the figure.)*\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Table : List of AERONET sites used for validation\n",
        "\n",
        "# Uncertainty Analysis Following FIDUCEO Approach\n",
        "\n",
        "## Primary Measurement Equation\n",
        "\n",
        "The TOC directional reflectance for each spectral band j is obtained through the SMAC atmospheric correction:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{aligned}\n",
        "R_{toc}\\left( \\theta_{s},\\theta_{v},\\Delta\\Phi \\right)\n",
        "&= f\\left( R_{toa},T_{g},T_{sca},R_{atm},s_{atm};U_{H_{2}O},U_{O_{3}},P_{s},\\tau_{a}^{550},aerosol\\_ model \\right) \\\\\n",
        "&\\quad + \\varepsilon_{0}\n",
        "\\end{aligned}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **R~toc~**: Top-of-Canopy directional reflectance (output)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **R~toa~**: Top-of-Atmosphere reflectance (primary input)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **T~g~**: Total gaseous transmission\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **T~sca~**: Atmospheric scattering transmission\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **R~atm~**: Atmospheric path reflectance\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **s~atm~**: Atmospheric spherical albedo\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **U~H₂O~**: Total column water vapor (auxiliary input from MERRA-2)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **U~O₃~**: Total column ozone (auxiliary input from MERRA-2)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **P~s~**: Surface pressure (derived from DEM and MERRA-2 SLP)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **τ~a~⁵⁵⁰**: Aerosol optical thickness at 550 nm (auxiliary input from MERRA-2)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **aerosol model**: Selected aerosol optical properties\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- **ε₀**: Second-order uncertainty terms\n",
        "\n",
        "## Primary Uncertainty Equation\n",
        "\n",
        "The total TOC reflectance uncertainty is derived from the measurement equation through uncertainty propagation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "u\\left( R_{toc}^{j} \\right)\n",
        "= \\sqrt{\n",
        "\\left( \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}^{j}}{\\partial R_{toa}^{j}}u(R_{toa}^{j}) \\right)^{2}\n",
        "+ \\left( \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}^{j}}{\\partial U_{H_2O}}u(U_{H_2O}) \\right)^{2}\n",
        "+ \\left( \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}^{j}}{\\partial U_{O_3}}u(U_{O_3}) \\right)^{2}\n",
        "}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\sqrt{\n",
        "\\left( \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}^{j}}{\\partial P_{S}}u(P_{S}) \\right)^{2}\n",
        "+ \\left( \\frac{\\partial R_{toc}^{j}}{\\partial \\tau_{a}^{550}}u\\left( \\tau_{a}^{550} \\right) \\right)^{2}\n",
        "+ \\left( u\\left( R_{toc}^{j} \\right)_{ensemble} \\right)^{2}\n",
        "+ \\left( u\\left( R_{toc}^{j} \\right)_{RTM} \\right)^{2}\n",
        "} + u^{2}(0)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "Where individual contributions include:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **TOA reflectance uncertainty** (from Level 1C, propagated with analytical Jacobians)\n",
        "- **Gaseous absorption uncertainties** (O₃, H₂O, propagated with analytical Jacobians)\n",
        "- **Surface pressure uncertainty** (from DEM + geolocation, propagated with finite difference)\n",
        "- **Aerosol optical depth uncertainty** (from MERRA-2 validation studies, propagated with finite difference)\n",
        "- **Aerosol model uncertainty** (from AMIP ensemble spread)\n",
        "- **Radiative transfer approximation errors** (SMAC vs. exact RT, terrain slope, adjacency...)\n",
        "- Second-order effects (u²(0) term)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Effects Tables (FIDUCEO Methodology)\n",
        "\n",
        "Following Popp and Mittaz (2022), each uncertainty source is characterized through \"effects tables\" documenting:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Affected term in measurement equation\n",
        "\n",
        "- Maturity of uncertainty estimate (0=none to 3=rigorous)\n",
        "\n",
        "- Correlation structure (type and scale, spatial and temporal)\n",
        "\n",
        "- PDF shape and magnitude\n",
        "\n",
        "- Sensitivity coefficients\n",
        "\n",
        "## TOA Reflectance Uncertainty\n",
        "\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Descriptor                   | Value                            | Notes                                        |\n",
        "+:=============================+:=================================+:=============================================+\n",
        "| Name                         | Direct TOA reflectance inversion |                                              |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Affected term                | R~toc~ = f(R~toa~)               |                                              |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Maturity                     | 3 - Rigorous analysis            | Direct propagation with analytical Jacobians |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Correlation type             | From Level 1C product            | Random, structured, common components        |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Correlation scale (spatial)  | Pixel-dependent                  | Structured: scan-line or column correlations |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Correlation scale (temporal) | Scene-independent                | Random component uncorrelated                |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| PDF shape                    | Gaussian                         | Assumed from calibration analysis            |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Magnitude                    | DTOA-r from L1C                  | Band-dependent, typically 0.01-0.03          |\n",
        "+------------------------------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n",
