        "\n",
        "### Aerosol Optical Depth Uncertainty\n",
        "\n",
        "Quantifying aerosol optical depth (AOD) uncertainty in global chemical transport models (CTMs) remains critical for climate and air quality applications. Recent studies have highlighted systematic biases and uncertainties in leading reanalysis products such as CAMS and MERRA-2.\n",
        "\n",
        "Comparative validation studies against AERONET ground-based observations reveal that both CAMS and MERRA-2 exhibit regional biases, with typical AOD uncertainties ranging from 30-50% depending on aerosol type and geographic location. Model-observation discrepancies are particularly pronounced over dust-dominated regions and biomass burning areas, where AOD can be underestimated by factors of 1.5-2.0.\n",
        "\n",
        "Advances in uncertainty quantification have emerged through ensemble approaches and data assimilation techniques. Studies show that assimilating satellite retrievals can reduce AOD uncertainty by 20-35%, though systematic errors in aerosol vertical distribution persist. Emission inventory uncertainties, particularly for anthropogenic sources in rapidly developing regions, can account for 25-40% of total AOD uncertainty.\n",
        "\n",
        "The community is moving toward probabilistic frameworks that explicitly quantify measurement uncertainties, model uncertainties, and structural uncertainties arising from parameterization choices in aerosol microphysics, chemistry, and removal processes.\n",
        "\n",
        "The AOD uncertainties (Root Mean Square Errors) could be assigned on a regional scale using a climate type classification map like the one used in Gueymard and Yang 2020. Years of AOD \\@550 and Angström exponent 3-hourly datasets from MERRA-2 and CAMS have been evaluated at 793 AERONET stations. The validation was conducted based on continents and Köppen-Geiger classification (see Figure 3).\n",
        "\n",
        "+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "|                                                                                                                                                           |\n",
        "+:==========================================================================================================================================================+\n",
        "| ![](./media/media/image5.png){width=\"5.479861111111111in\" height=\"3.6in\"} |\n",
        "+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "Figure : Map of Köppen-Geiger climate classification\n",
        "\n",
        "#### RMSE Model\n",
        "\n",
        "Based on the Gueymard and Yang findings, a practical operational uncertainty predictor can be formulated as:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\sigma\\left( \\tau_{a}^{550} \\right) = \\max\\left( \\sigma_{base},\\sigma_{relative} \\times \\tau_{a}^{550} \\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- σ~base~ = 0.03 (clean atmosphere baseline)\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- σ~relative~ = 0.15 (15% relative uncertainty)\n",
        "\n",
        "This is justified by the following arguments\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- Low AOD regime (τ~a~ \\< 0.2): Dominated by instrument noise \\~0.03\n",
        "\n",
        "\\- Moderate-high AOD (τ~a~ ≥ 0.2): Scales with aerosol loading → 15% uncertainty\n",
        "\n",
        "We intend in an **updated version** to apply Köppen-Geiger climate classification multipliers:\n",
        "\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "| Region Type          | Multiplier     | Example Locations          |\n",
        "+:=====================+:===============+:===========================+\n",
        "| Oceanic/Polar        | 0.7×           | Open oceans, Arctic        |\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "| North America/Europe | 1.0×           | Baseline reference         |\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "| Dust-dominated       | 1.5×           | Sahara, Arabian Peninsula  |\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "| Biomass burning      | 1.4×           | Amazon, Sub-Saharan Africa |\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "| High pollution       | 1.3×           | East Asia, South Asia      |\n",
        "+----------------------+----------------+----------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "+------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Descriptor                   | Value                                                                                | Notes                               |\n",
        "+:=============================+:=====================================================================================+:====================================+\n",
        "| Name                         | AOD at 550 nm uncertainty                                                            |                                     |\n",
        "+------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Affected term                | Rtoc = f(τ~a~⁵⁵⁰)                                                                    |                                     |\n",
        "+------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Maturity                     | 3 - Based on comprehensive validation                                                | Gueymard & Yang (2020) study        |\n",
