        "## Radiative Transfer Approximations\n",
        "\n",
        "Three sources of RT approximation errors:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Lambertian Surface Assumption\n",
        "\n",
        "It is most important for NIR and strong aerosol loading (in that case uncertainty due to AOD dominating). The modelling of the effect and a way to estimate the uncertainty associated is described in section 8.5. The surface BRDF shape is modeled using two parameters ${\\ k}_{1}^{p}$ and $k_{2}^{p}$, depending on spectral band.\n",
        "\n",
        "In the baseline run, the surface is supposed to be lambertian (in that case${\\ k}_{1}^{p} = k_{2}^{p} = 0$). In a second run, those two parameters are assigned a climatological value, for example coming from the C3S Multi Sensor Surface Albedo products k~0~, k~1~ and k~2~ with $k_{1}^{p} = \\ \\frac{k_{1}}{k_{0}}\\ ;\\ k_{2}^{p} = \\ \\frac{k_{2}}{k_{0}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "Difference in R~toc~ from the two runs gives an estimation of the BRDF effects.\n",
        "\n",
        "$u\\left( R_{toc}^{j} \\right)_{RTM\\_BRDF} = \\left( {\\ k}_{1}^{p}=0,k_{2}^{p} =0 \\right) - \\left( {\\ k}_{1}^{p} \\neq 0, k_{2}^{p} \\neq 0 \\right)$\n",
        "+--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Descriptor   | Value                                                                                                                                                                | Notes                               |\n",
        "+:=============+:=====================================================================================================================================================================+:====================================+\n",
        "| Significance | Moderate (NIR, high AOD)                                                                                                                                             |                                     |\n",
        "+--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Maturity     | 1 - Initial assessment                                                                                                                                               | From 6S validation                  |\n",
        "+--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Magnitude    | \\~1% for most cases                                                                                                                                                  | Up to 5% for strong BRDF + high AOD |\n",
        "+--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Mitigation   | Using BRDF shape included in the product (https://dast.copernicus-climate.eu/documents/satellite-albedo/D1.3.4-v2.0_ATBD_CDR_SA_MULTI_SENSOR_v2.0_PRODUCTS_v1.1.pdf) |                                     |\n",
        "+--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "Table : RTM Lambertian assumption uncertainty summary\n",
        "\n",
        "### Terrain Slope Effects\n",
        "\n",
        "Mountain areas, rough terrain, have been modelled and estimated through a simple model following [cesbio](https://www.cesbio.cnrs.fr/multitemp/2481/) (https://www.cesbio.cnrs.fr/multitemp/2481/)\n",
        "\n",
        "The slope_eff function computes the terrain-induced relative effect. Here are the mathematical equations:\n",
        "\n",
        "[Input Variables:]{.underline}\n",
        "\n",
        "- $\\theta_{s}$ : Solar Zenith Angle (SZA)\n",
        "\n",
        "- $\\phi_{s}$ : Solar Azimuth Angle (SAA)\n",
        "\n",
        "- $s$ : Terrain slope (computed from DEM using xdem python package)\n",
        "\n",
        "- $\\phi_{a}$ : Terrain aspect (computed from DEM using xdem python package)\n",
        "\n",
        "[Derived Quantities:]{.underline}\n",
        "\n",
        "- Cosine of solar zenith angle:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mu_{s} = cos\\left( \\theta_{s} \\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- Cosine of terrain slope:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mu = cos(s)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- Effective cosine of incidence angle on tilted surface:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mu_{i} = \\mu_{s} \\cdot \\mu + \\sqrt{1 - \\mu_{s}^{2}} \\cdot \\sqrt{1 - \\mu^{2}} \\cdot cos\\left( \\phi_{s} - \\phi_{a} \\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- Sky view factor:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$f_{sky} = \\frac{1 + \\mu}{2}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- Ground view factor:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$f_{ground} = \\frac{1 - \\mu}{2}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- Slope Error\n",
        "\n",
        "$$slope_{eff} = \\frac{T}{T_{dir} \\cdot \\frac{\\mu_{i}}{\\mu_{s}} + T_{dif} \\cdot f_{sky} + T \\cdot f_{ground} \\cdot \\rho_{env}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- ${u\\left( R_{toc}^{j} \\right)}_{RTM - slope} = R_{toc}^{j}*(slope_{eff} - 1)$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "\n",
        "$T$ : Total atmospheric transmittance (an output of the SMAC function)\n",
        "\n",
        "$T_{dir}$ : Direct atmospheric transmittance (an output of the SMAC function)\n",
        "\n",
        "$T_{dif}$ : Diffuse atmospheric transmittance (an output of the SMAC function)\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\rho_{env}:$ Average environment reflectance, (supposed here equal to pixel ground reflectance)\n",
        "\n",
        "+--------------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Descriptor   | Value                                   | Notes                               |\n",
        "+:=============+:========================================+:====================================+\n",
        "| Significance | Moderate to High in mountainous regions |                                     |\n",
        "+--------------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Maturity     | 1 - Initial assessment                  | From CESBIO simple model (see text) |\n",
        "+--------------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Magnitude    | Several %                               | Could be 40%                        |\n",
        "+--------------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "| Mitigation   | Simple model                            | From CESBIO simple model (see text) |\n",
        "+--------------+-----------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+\n",
        "\n",
        "Table : RTM terrain effect uncertainty summary\n",
