        "# Conclusions\n",
        "\n",
        "This ATBD demonstrates a comprehensive implementation of the FIDUCEO uncertainty propagation methodology for atmospheric correction of satellite vegetation sensors. Key achievements:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Rigorous Uncertainty Quantification**: All major uncertainty sources are identified, characterized, and propagated through the measurement equation\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Operational AOD Uncertainty Model**: Based on extensive MERRA-2 validation (Gueymard & Yang 2020), providing realistic AOD uncertainties: σ(τ~a~) = max(0.03, 0.15×τa) with regional adjustments\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Ensemble Approach for Model Uncertainty**: AMIP 10-member ensemble quantifies aerosol optical property uncertainties\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Efficient GPU Implementation**: SMAC-CL enables fast processing while computing full Jacobian matrices\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Validation Framework**: Following Aerosol_cci and FIDUCEO best practices (Popp & Mittaz 2022)\n",
        "\n",
        "This approach provides climate-quality TOC reflectances with fully traceable, metrologically sound uncertainties suitable for:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Long-term surface monitoring\n",
        "\n",
        "- Multi-sensor harmonization\n",
        "\n",
