        "\n",
        "# Appendix C: SMAC-CL Implementation\n",
        "\n",
        "## Input reading\n",
        "\n",
        "The elevation map and its uncertainty (elev and Delev) are read from the DEM auxiliary file [once]{.underline} ( see section 2.2).\n",
        "\n",
        "The image inputs are read from Level 1 files (Section 2.1). For each pixel of the image, the following quantities are read:\n",
        "\n",
        "- The TOA radiance for each sensor channel *λ*: TOA-r(*λ*)\n",
        "\n",
        "- The corresponding error: DTOA-r(*λ*),\n",
        "\n",
        "- The corresponding solar extra-terrestrial irradiance Es(*λ*)\n",
        "\n",
        "- The sun zenith angle (SZA), the sun azimuth angle (SAA), the view zenith angles (VZA, VZA_SWIR), and the viewing azimuth angle (VAA, VAA_SWIR),\n",
        "\n",
        "- The latitude and longitude: lat, lon*,*\n",
        "\n",
        "The [name of the sensor, date and mean time of acquisition (in UTC)]{.underline} should be written in the file as an [attribute]{.underline}. Indeed, the name of the sensor and the date of acquisition allow reading the right SMAC coefficients coeffs while the date allows reading the daily MERRA-2 auxiliary files as described in Section 2.3 and monthly AMIP auxiliary files as described in Section 2.4.\n",
        "\n",
        "If the BRDF effects estimation is activated in the configuration, then we build the right name for auxiliary C3S Surface Albedo product as in section 2.6 .\n",
        "\n",
        "## Pixel masking\n",
        "\n",
        "The cloud contaminated are masked and not further processed. The selection is based on the cloud flag already present in the input file. The idea is to keep [the clearest pixels only]{.underline}. It is done by selecting pixels for which the flag is 0. We mask out also pixels for which SZA is above 90°.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Spatial and temporal interpolation of auxiliary data\n",
        "\n",
        "From elev, Delev, lat, lon, the pixel altitude **z** and its uncertainty **∆z** is obtained through a [nearest neighbor interpolation]{.underline}.\n",
        "\n",
        "The sea-level pressure **P~0~**, the temperature above ground **T**, the total ozone column$\\ \\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{O}_{\\mathbf{3}}}$, the total column water vapor$\\ \\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{H}_{\\mathbf{2}}\\mathbf{O}}$ and the AOT at 550 nm $\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$ , $\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;DU}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;SU}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;OC}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;BC}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;SS}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$are obtained respectively from the SLP, T10M, TO3, TQV and TOTEXTTAU, DUEXTTAU, SUEXTTAU, OCEXTTAU, BCEXTTAU, SSEXTTAU MERRA-2 auxiliary data (see section2.3) through a [spatial and temporal linear interpolation]{.underline}\n",
        "\n",
        "Then the monthly means of aerosol optical thicknesses coming from the AMIP 10 runs are loaded and [spatially interpolated]{.underline} to give $\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$ ,\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;DU;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;SU;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;OC;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;BC;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}\\mathbf{,}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a;SS;AMIPj}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$ for **model run number j**. The fields TOTEXTTAU, DUEXTTAU, SUEXTTAU, OCEXTTAU, BCEXTTAU, SSEXTTAU from the AMIP auxiliary files are used (see section 2.4**Erreur ! Source du renvoi introuvable.**)\n",
        "\n",
        "The auxiliary data is then converted from MERRA-2 to SMAC units:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  Table: MERRA-2 and SMAC units\n",
        "\n",
        "| Variable | MERRA-2 unit | SMAC unit | Conversion factor |\n",
        "|:---------|:-------------|:----------|:------------------|\n",
        "| U~O3~    | Dobson       | cm.atm    | 1e-3              |\n",
        "| U~H2O~   | kg.m^-2^     | g.cm^-2^  | 1e-1              |\n",
        "| P~0~     | Pa           | hPa       | 1e-2              |\n",
        "\n",
        "Then, the surface pressure **P~s~** and its uncertainty **∆P~s~** are computed using Eq. (20), (21), and (22), (23), (24).\n",
        "\n",
        "Interpolate spatially to have BRDF parameters k~1p~ and k~2p~\n",
        "\n",
        "## Aerosols models selections\n",
        "\n",
        "Select the aerosol model number (between 148 models), by minimizing the distance in a 5-dimensional space corresponding to the 5 AOT ratios {X~u~, u$\\  \\in \\{ DU,SU,OC,BC,SS\\ \\}$} of the 5 aerosol components\n",
        "\n",
        "X~u~ = $\\frac{\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}\\mathbf{;}\\mathbf{u}}^{\\mathbf{550}}}{\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "**iaero** = $\\text{argmin}_i \\sum_{u} \\left(X_u - X_{u,i}\\right)^{2}$, for $i=0,\\ldots,147$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The X~u,i~ basis for the 148 predefined models are stored in a text file and read once.\n",
        "\n",
        "An example of interpolated inputs is given in Figure 17 : Example of inputs ancillary atmospheric data for a VGT sub-image\n",
        "\n",
        "The list of aerosol models of AMIP are also computed using the same approach to give **iaero~AMIPj~** for j in 1...10\n",
        "\n",
        "## SMAC-CL function\n",
        "\n",
        "**Architecture:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Language: OpenCL (compatible with GPU and CPU)\n",
        "- Interface: Python wrapper\n",
        "- Processing mode: Pixel-parallel (massively parallel on GPU)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Main Processing Function:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "def smac_cl_run(\n",
        "    coeffs,           # SMAC coefficients (148 aerosol models)\n",
        "    tetas, tetav,     # SZA, VZA arrays\n",
        "    phis, phiv,       # SAA, VAA arrays\n",
        "    uh2o, uo3,        # Water vapor, ozone columns\n",
        "    taup550,          # AOD at 550 nm\n",
        "    pressure,         # Surface pressure\n",
        "    rtoa,             # TOA reflectance\n",
        "    k1p, k2p,         # BRDF kernel ratios (default 0 for Lambertian)\n",
        "    iaero_list        # List of aerosol model indices (11 models)\n",
        "):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Inputs: All arrays dimensioned [npixels] or [nbands, npixels]\n",
        "    Outputs:\n",
        "      - rtoc: TOC reflectance [nbands, npixels]\n",
        "      - jacobians: Sensitivity matrices\n",
        "      - u_ensemble: Std dev from aerosol ensemble\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Processing Flow:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│  1. Reorganize input arrays for GPU efficiency      │\n",
        "│     (transpose, flatten, pad)                       │\n",
        "└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                   │\n",
        "                   ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│  2. Upload data to GPU/CPU memory                   │\n",
        "│     - TOA reflectances                              │\n",
        "│     - Geometry arrays                               │\n",
        "│     - Auxiliary data (UH₂O, UO₃, Ps, τa)            │\n",
        "│     - SMAC coefficients (pre-loaded once)           │\n",
        "└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                   │\n",
        "                   ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│  3. GPU/CPU kernel execution (per-pixel parallel)   │\n",
        "│     For each pixel in parallel:                     │\n",
        "│       a. Compute gaseous transmissions              │\n",
        "│       b. Compute Rayleigh scattering                │\n",
        "│       c. Compute aerosol scattering                 │\n",
        "│       d. Apply SMAC equations → Rtoc                │\n",
        "│       e. Compute analytical Jacobians               │\n",
        "│       f. Repeat for finite-difference Jacobians     │\n",
        "│       g. Repeat for 10 aerosol ensemble members     │\n",
        "└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                   │\n",
        "                   ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│  4. Download results from GPU/CPU                   │\n",
        "│     - Rtoc arrays                                   │\n",
        "│     - Jacobian arrays                               │\n",
        "│     - Ensemble statistics                           │\n",
        "└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "                   │\n",
        "                   ▼\n",
        "┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n",
        "│  5. CPU post-processing                             │\n",
        "│     - Combine uncertainty components                │\n",
        "│     - Apply terrain corrections                     │\n",
        "│     - Quality flag assignment                       │\n",
        "└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "![](./media/media/image35.png){width=\"6.873611111111111in\" height=\"3.8402777777777777in\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "**Performance:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- GPU acceleration: \\~100× faster than CPU for large images\n",
        "- Memory requirement: \\~2 GB GPU RAM for full-swath processing\n",
        "- Typical processing time: \\<TBD second per tile (1000×1000 pixels)\n",
        "\n",
        "The SMAC-CL run procedure inputs correspond to the following quantities described in this document:\n",
        "\n",
        "coeffs, SZA, VZA, SAA, VAA,$\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{H}_{\\mathbf{2}}\\mathbf{O}}$,$\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{O}_{\\mathbf{3}}}$,$\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$, **P~s~**, TOA-r(*λ*), k1p, k2p, iaero_list.\n",
        "\n",
        "The run method is called twice, one for the VIS-NIR bands and one for the SWIR band. iaero_list contains 11 aerosol model number. The first one is iaero, the 10 others are iaero_AMIPj ( see section 10.4).\n",
        "\n",
        "Upon selection in the configuration, the k1p and k2p arrays are set to zero, that means that the surface is considered lambertian. A call with these coefficients not set to zero, for example using L3 BRDF products allows to estimate the effect of BRDF on the TOC-r\n",
        "\n",
        "All the image inputs are multidimensional\n",
        "\n",
        "The outputs of the SMAC-CL run routine are:\n",
        "\n",
        "- The AC corrected directional reflectance $\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}$ for each sensor channel *λ*\n",
        "\n",
        "- The Jacobians$\\ \\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toa}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{O}_{\\mathbf{3}}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{H}_{\\mathbf{2}}\\mathbf{O}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{P}_{\\mathbf{S}}}}\\mathbf{\\ ,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}}$ for each sensor channel *λ*\n",
        "\n",
        "- The standard deviation ${\\mathbf{u}\\left( \\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}} \\right)}_{\\mathbf{ensemble}}$ due to aerosol models spread for each sensor channel *λ*\n",
        "\n",
        "An example of the outputs and Jacobians is given in Figure 18\n",
        "\n",
        "## Level 2A Output Variables\n",
        "\n",
        "The standard outputs of AC module are:\n",
        "\n",
        "- The AC corrected directional reflectance $\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}$ for each sensor channel *λ*,\n",
        "\n",
        "- The associated uncertainties $\\mathbf{\\mathrm{\\Delta}}\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}$for each sensor channel *λ*,\n",
        "\n",
        "- Flags\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 0 : cloud \\_contaminated (clm != 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 1 : High AOD (TOA \\>= 0.6)\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 2 : High SZA (sza \\> 80.)\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 3 : High AOD gradient (aod_grad \\> Threshold)\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 4 : AC algorithm failure\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 5 : Missing auxiliary data\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Bit 6 : Out of LUT range\n",
        "\n",
        "TOC directional reflectances and Jacobians are direct outputs of the SMAC procedure (done in the GPU) while the [associated uncertainties are post-processed in the CPU]{.underline} as described in section 5.2. The quantities used are:\n",
        "\n",
        "- The Jacobians $\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toa}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{O}_{\\mathbf{3}}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{H}_{\\mathbf{2}}\\mathbf{O}}}\\mathbf{,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{P}_{\\mathbf{S}}}}\\mathbf{\\ ,\\ }\\mathbf{J}_{\\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}}}^{\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "- DTOA-r(*λ*), $\\mathrm{\\Delta}\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{O}_{\\mathbf{3}}}$, $\\mathrm{\\Delta}\\mathbf{U}_{\\mathbf{H}_{\\mathbf{2}}\\mathbf{O}}$, $\\mathrm{\\Delta}\\mathbf{P}_{\\mathbf{S}}$, $\\mathrm{\\Delta}\\mathbf{\\tau}_{\\mathbf{a}}^{\\mathbf{550}}$)\n",
        "\n",
        "- ${\\mathbf{u}\\left( \\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}} \\right)}_{\\mathbf{ensemble}}$**, slope_error,** ${\\mathbf{u}\\left( \\mathbf{R}_{\\mathbf{toc}} \\right)}_{\\mathbf{RTM}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "The projection and the attributes of the input TOA reflectances are kept. Nevertheless, the longitude and latitude fields are also written in the output file for simplicity.\n",
        "\n",
        "An example of the outputs is given in.\n",
        "\n",
