        "## Performance Optimizations\n",
        "\n",
        "### Ancillary Zarr Cache\n",
        "\n",
        "| Aspect | Description |\n",
        "|----|----|\n",
        "| What | Pre-interpolates MERRA-2 fields to the full satellite grid once, stores them in a local Zarr cache |\n",
        "| Why | MERRA-2 source files sit on network storage; per-tile interpolation would re-read the network and repeat work |\n",
        "| Function | `precompute_ancillary()` in `process.py` |\n",
        "| Toggle | `[Sizes] anc_cache` (default on) |\n",
        "| Numerical equivalence | Pointwise interpolation → identical to per-tile interpolation (tiles read from local cache with halo) |\n",
        "| Memory | Streamed tile-by-tile to bound peak memory (\\~2.8 GB, safe on 4 GB nodes) |\n",
        "\n",
        ": Ancillary Zarr cache optimization\n",
        "\n",
        "Cache format: Zarr format 2. Most fields are stored as float16 (small values, sufficient precision); `SLP` and `T10M` are stored as float32 (see D.2, overflow protection).\n",
