        "\n",
        ": Output NetCDF global attributes\n",
        "\n",
        "Each variable also carries `standard_name`, `units`, `long_name`, and `comments` attributes from the CF JSON configuration. The output NetCDF is written with chunk sizes matching the tile processing grid, ensuring efficient random access for downstream consumers.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Appendix E: SMACCL OpenCL Kernel API (NEW in v1.1)\n",
        "\n",
        "This appendix documents the SMACCL OpenCL function API as implemented in the HYGEOS `smaccl` repository (OpenCL branch), covering both the Python host wrapper API (`smaccl/smaccl.py`, class `Smaccl`) and the OpenCL kernel API (`smaccl/devicecl.cl`, kernel `smaccl`). It complements the description of the SMAC-CL function given in Appendix C.5, providing a precise implementation-facing contract for integration and maintenance.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Python Host API\n",
        "\n",
        "**Signature:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "def run(\n",
        "    self,\n",
        "    coeffs,\n",
        "    tetas, tetav,\n",
        "    phis, phiv,\n",
        "    uh2o, uo3,\n",
        "    taup550, pression,\n",
        "    rtoa,\n",
        "    k1p, k2p,\n",
        "    iaero,\n",
        "    NBLOOP=1,\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Returned tuple:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "(rsurf, rsurf_0, dev_std, Jrtoa, Juo3, Juh2o, Jpre, Jtaup)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "All returned arrays are float32 and shaped like `rtoa`.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input semantics:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- `coeffs`: SMAC coefficients; the first dimension defines the number of spectral bands processed.\n",
        "- `tetas`, `tetav`: solar and view zenith angles (SZA, VZA), float32.\n",
        "- `phis`, `phiv`: solar and view azimuth angles (SAA, VAA), float32.\n",
        "- `uh2o`, `uo3`: total water vapor and ozone columns, float32.\n",
        "- `taup550`: aerosol optical depth at 550 nm, float32.\n",
        "- `pression`: surface pressure, float32.\n",
        "- `rtoa`: TOA reflectance, float32.\n",
        "- `k1p`, `k2p`: BRDF normalized kernel ratios (0 for Lambertian processing).\n",
        "- `iaero`: aerosol model indices per pixel, with `Naero` candidates.\n",
        "- `NBLOOP`: number of internal per-thread loops (repeated runs / Monte-Carlo patterns).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Shape contract** (4D tensor layout for tiled processing):\n",
        "\n",
        "| Array | Shape |\n",
        "|----|----|\n",
        "| `rtoa` | (NBAND, NZ, XBLOCK, XGRID) |\n",
        "| `tetas`, `tetav`, `phis`, `phiv`, `uh2o`, `uo3`, `taup550`, `pression` | (NZ, XBLOCK, XGRID) |\n",
        "| `k1p`, `k2p` | (NBAND, NZ, XBLOCK, XGRID) |\n",
        "| `iaero` | (Naero, NZ, XBLOCK, XGRID) |\n",
        "\n",
        ": SMACCL host API shape contract\n",
        "\n",
        "Where `NBAND` is the number of spectral bands handled in the call, `NZ` is the padded depth along the pixel-index dimension, `XBLOCK`/`XGRID` control the OpenCL launch decomposition, and `Naero` is the number of aerosol candidates used in the ensemble/selection.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Runtime behavior:** (1) allocate output buffers for `rsurf`, `rsurf_0`, `dev_std` and the Jacobians; (2) copy host arrays to OpenCL buffers; (3) launch the OpenCL kernel `smaccl`; (4) copy outputs from device to host arrays.\n",
        "\n",
        "## OpenCL Kernel API\n",
        "\n",
        "**Signature (`devicecl.cl`):**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "__kernel void smaccl(\n",
        "    __global coef_atmos *ca,\n",
        "    __global float *tetas_, __global float *tetav_,\n",
        "    __global float *phis_,  __global float *phiv_,\n",
        "    __global float *uh2o_,  __global float *uo3_,\n",
        "    __global float *taup550_, __global float *pression_,\n",
        "    __global float *rtoa_,\n",
        "    __global float *rsurf,\n",
        "    __global float *Jr,  __global float *Juo3,\n",
        "    __global float *Juh2o, __global float *Jpre,\n",
        "    __global float *Jtaup,\n",
        "    __global float *k1p_, __global float *k2p_,\n",
        "    __global int *iaero,\n",
        "    int NMOD, int NBLOOPd, int NBANDd, int NZd\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Kernel-level constants and finite differences:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- `dpre = 10.0` hPa for the pressure Jacobian finite difference\n",
        "- `dtau_rel = 0.1` for the relative AOD perturbation\n",
        "- `NRUN = 3 + NBLOOPd`: 1 reference run + 2 perturbation runs for the finite-difference Jacobians ($P_s$, $\\tau_{550}$) + `NBLOOPd` optional additional looped runs\n",
        "\n",
        "## Output Mapping\n",
        "\n",
        "The host API output tuple maps to the AC physics described in Sections 3 and 5 as follows:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Host variable | Physical meaning                                 |\n",
        "|---------------|--------------------------------------------------|\n",
        "| `rsurf`       | TOC directional reflectance (`rTOC`)             |\n",
        "| `rsurf_0`     | Lambertian-equivalent TOC reflectance (`rTOC_0`) |\n",
        "| `dev_std`     | Aerosol-model ensemble spread (`UrTOC_ens`)      |\n",
        "| `Jrtoa`       | Jacobian $\\partial R_{toc}/\\partial R_{toa}$     |\n",
        "| `Juo3`        | Jacobian $\\partial R_{toc}/\\partial U_{O3}$      |\n",
        "| `Juh2o`       | Jacobian $\\partial R_{toc}/\\partial U_{H2O}$     |\n",
        "| `Jpre`        | Jacobian $\\partial R_{toc}/\\partial P_s$         |\n",
        "| `Jtaup`       | Jacobian $\\partial R_{toc}/\\partial \\tau_{550}$  |\n",
        "\n",
        ": SMACCL kernel output variable mapping\n",
        "\n",
        "## ISmaccl Wrapper API\n",
        "\n",
        "The integration layer `ISmaccl` wraps the kernel API for product-level execution.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Constructor:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "ISmaccl(\n",
        "    config, frac_aer_model, ca,\n",
        "    XBLOCK=128, XGRID=128,\n",
        "    breakpoint=False, ancillary=False,\n",
        "    platform=...,   # forwarded to Smaccl(platform=...)\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Product-level methods:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- `run_block(l2_data, batch_size=512)`: block mapping over xarray/dask chunks.\n",
        "- `run(l2_data, iaero)`: scene/tile execution and assembly of the xarray output dataset.\n",
        "- `exec_smaccl(...)`: low-level preparation/padding/reshaping, kernel call, post-mapping.\n",
        "\n",
        "**`exec_smaccl` returned tuple:**\n",
        "\n",
        "```         \n",
        "(\n",
        "    rsurf, rsurf0, dev_std,\n",
        "    Juh2o, Juo3, Jrtoa, Jpre, Jtaup,\n",
        "    Duh2o, Duo3, Drtoa, Dpre, Dtaup,\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "This extends the kernel outputs by including uncertainty-input terms (`D*`) computed on the host side for subsequent propagation (see the Uncertainty Analysis section).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Band handling in Proba-V mode:** the wrapper executes two calls — a VIS/NIR group using `VZA`/`VAA`, and a SWIR group using `VZA_IR`/`VAA_IR` — then merges the outputs into full 4-band products.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Device and Data Contracts\n",
        "\n",
        "**Data type and ordering requirements:** arrays are converted to C-order contiguous layout; floating inputs are cast to float32; the aerosol index array is cast to integer (int16/int32 depending on the processing stage); invalid geolocation values are sanitized before kernel packing; padded extended arrays (`GSIZEXT`) are filled with NaN then reshaped to the launch geometry.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Device and queue selection:** `Smaccl.__init__` compiles the kernel source and creates the queue/context via `set_queue(xpu, environment)`. The repository implementation supports the following environment mapping:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Environment  | CPU device name             | GPU device name |\n",
        "|--------------|-----------------------------|-----------------|\n",
        "| `Default`    | Portable Computing Language | NVIDIA CUDA     |\n",
        "| `Turenne`    | Intel(R) OpenCL             | —               |\n",
        "| `TerraScope` | Intel(R) OpenCL             | NVIDIA CUDA     |\n",
        "\n",
        ": OpenCL device/environment mapping\n",
        "\n",
        "If no compatible/available device is found, initialization fails.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Contractual outputs for FDR4VGT:** for this ATBD, the contractual kernel-facing outputs are the reflectance (`rTOC`, `rTOC_0`), the Jacobians (`Jrtoa`, `Juo3`, `Juh2o`, `Jpre`, `Jtau550`), and the aerosol spread (`UrTOC_ens`). Host-side uncertainty terms (`Duh2o`, `Duo3`, `Drtoa`, `Dpre`, `Dtaup`) are combined with these Jacobians in the uncertainty propagation equation of Section 5. This appendix defines the implementation API used by the operational chain and should be updated if the upstream HYGEOS `smaccl` API changes."
